# scrub-terms.local — copy this to `scrub-terms.local` (gitignored) and add YOUR
# private identifiers. `python scripts/scrub_check.py` FAILS on any match, so run
# it before publishing / pushing.
#
# One Python regex per line. Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
# Add the distinctive strings that must never leak into a public repo:
#   - employer / organization names
#   - internal product or repository names
#   - your work email domain, and your own name / usernames
#   - internal hostnames or service names
#
# Examples (PLACEHOLDERS — replace with your own):
# acme-corp
# acmehq
# \binternal-service-name\b
# @acme\.com
# \bjdoe\b
